name: Jan David Zocher the Younger
biography: He trained in Paris at the Ecole des Beaux Arts before traveling to Italy, Switzerland, and England. After returning to Holland in 1817, both he and his father, Jan David Zocher the Elder, as well as his son, Louis Paul Zocher, developed the landscape park garden style in Holland. In addition to small private commissions, Zocher achieved fame for his grdens at Twinckel and Rosendael.
